\subsubsection{Planck TT+lowP}
We report our results from the Planck TT+lowP dataset alone and combined with external datasets in Tab.~\ref{tab:nupert_TT1}, while in Fig.~\ref{fig:1d_pchip_nupert} the one-dimensional posterior probabilities for the most relevant cosmological parameters are depicted.
Notice that, in general, the limits are stable with respect to the choice of the dataset. Including information about the large scale structure of the universe (both in terms of the geometrical BAO and the matter power spectrum shape) leads to tighter  constraints. This increased sensitivity is particularly evident for ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}$ and ${\ensuremath{P_{s,{i}}}}$ with $i\ge5$. For what concerns the former parameter, we can exclude ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}=1$ at more than 2$\sigma$ CL, with ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}=0.46^{+0.39}_{-0.34}$ for CMB+MPkW and ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}=0.52^{+0.39}_{-0.33}$ for CMB+BAO (both at $95\%$~CL). For the latter data combination, the scales corresponding to ${\ensuremath{P_{s,{11}}}}$ are efficiently probed by the matter power spectrum shape measurements, providing ${\ensuremath{P_{s,{11}}}}=0.95^{+0.60}_{-0.50}$ at 95\% CL. The combination of CMB+MPkW is indeed mildly sensitive to even smaller scales, yielding an upper limit for the last node ${\ensuremath{P_{s,{12}}}}<6.6$ at 95\% CL. Therefore, the inclusion of the MPkW dataset (and, to a minor extent, of the BAO measurements) allows to test smaller scales than those tested via CMB measurements alone.

Finally, we notice that the inclusion of the lensing likelihood helps in tightening the constraints on ${\ensuremath{P_{s,{i}}}}$ with $i\ge5$ as well, while the bounds on the neutrino parameters are only marginally improved with respect to the CMB-only dataset. In particular, the main effect is to push the lower bound on ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}$ towards higher values, in perfect agreement to what was  obtained by including BAO information (notice the overlap of the posterior distributions for ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}$ for the CMB+BAO and the CMB+lensing data combinations when ${\ensuremath{c^2_{\textrm{vis}}}}<0.31$ in Fig.~\ref{fig:1d_pchip_nupert}).

